# Deliberately empty. This file is mounted over `/app/.env` in the `test`
# service (see compose.yaml) so the test container cannot read the real one.
#
# Without it the security boundary leaks. The `test` service gets no
# `DATABASE_URL` in its environment, but the source tree is bind-mounted at
# /app, and the developer's real `.env` --- which holds the production
# connection string --- sits at the root of that tree. `env.load_env` reads
# `Path(__file__).parent / ".env"` unconditionally, so any call to
# `db.connection_string()` without an explicit environ mapping would pull
# production credentials into the process that TRUNCATEs the pipeline tables.
#
# No current call site does that; every one passes an explicit mapping. But the
# migrated Sales history has no backup, so this is enforced structurally rather
# than left to convention holding.
#
# Mounting an empty file (rather than, say, setting an empty DATABASE_URL) also
# keeps `DATABASE_URL` genuinely absent from the test environment, which is what
# ticket 01 asks for. A missing value fails loudly in `env.require`; a
# production one would not fail at all.
